        <p id="_Cyndi_s_Take_Cyndi_Bird_wife_Randy_first_caught_my_attenti">
        <span id="textspand6">Cyndi's Take<br /></span><span id="textspand7">Cyndi Bird, wife<br /></span><span id="textspand8"> <br />Randy first caught my attention when we were in college. The first memories I have of him were at our church. That's where I saw him with a group of four to five guys, and he was just very pleasant. I think that would be the right word to explain his personality. He was very friendly to everybody and I noticed that. He was nice to everybody, kind and you always saw him happy. It wasn't like he was overly in your face or always bubbly, but you could tell he was content and at peace with himself. All of these things together were what I think was an outward expression of feeling good inside about himself and that really attracted me to him. It definitely caught my eye.</span>
        </p>
        <%= image_tag("bachelor.png", :id => "bachelor", :class => "image") %>
        <p id="He_helped_to_organize_a_lot_of_activities_at_church_and_I_liked">
        He helped to organize a lot of activities at church and I liked that about him, too. I thought, Oh he's involved and social. It was really important to me that he be kind to everybody, not just certain people, and include everyone. He was really good that way and very involved. <br /><br />He was also very good looking, I thought, very handsome, and dressed really nice. That was important to me too, but I found out later it was his mother who dressed him so well, which was kind of funny. That's actually something about him that I, in a strange way, admire. He doesn't overly care about that sort of thing. That's something that I really like. I like him to dress nice, things like that, but it's not important to him. Things aren't that important to him and how he appears to others is not that important to him, as far as trying to impress people goes. <br /><br />I remember my brother one time saying, “Randy is a man with no guile.” I thought that is so true. I don't know if it's because I'm a woman, but I think a lot of it is. Women care a little more about what we look like and how we appear to people and we get kind of openly judged by that sometimes. I'm always a little bit more concerned about those kinds of things, but he doesn't let that kind of thing bother him at all. He didn't care if I had makeup on or didn't or in my grubby t-shirt and jeans or in a beautiful nice dress. He liked me either way, and I always appreciated that. <br />
        </p>
