        <p id="I_think_the_other_thing_about_Randy_that_I_really_liked_over_th">
        I think the other thing about Randy that I really liked over the years is he's a really, really hard worker. His fathers and his brothers taught him that, how to work hard, and that's been a huge blessing to me. The most important thing about that is the reason we work hard is for our family and to be able to help others eventually, too. That's what he did everything for: for his children, to take care of them and me and to be able to give to other people in need. That's why he wanted his own business, so he could help other people, employ other people and help them out and have control of his time. Then he could have more time with our children and with me when he wanted it and when he could and that was really important to me. <br /><br />That was probably one of things that I was looking for in a husband, someone that would not be gone all the time. I wanted a husband to be around that could help me raise our children together and not me by myself. So I was really glad that he felt the same way. 
        </p>
