        <span id="textspand9">Thirty-Four Years<br /></span><span id="textspand10"><br /></span><span id="textspand11">Our children ask us how our marriage turned out as successfully as it did. One of the contributing factors to the success is that we never once considered that we wouldn’t have a marriage. We were married in our church’s temple for time and all eternity and that’s what we expected of each other and never thought any differently. The thought never even entered my head. Even in our weaknesses, we knew that we needed each other, that we were compatible and that we could be a good team in raising our children. </span><br />
        </p>
